FOOT & MOUTH DISEASE - CHINA (09)
*********************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
Date: 23 June 2006
From: Yang Li <yangli@neuro-hemin.com>
Source: Ministry of Agriculture, China [Trans. from Chinese by
submitter] [edited]
<http://www.agri.gov.cn/ztzl/fkqlg/yqfb/t20060623_636093.htm>

The Ministry Of Agriculture [MOA] of China has announced an Asia type
I FMD outbreak confirmed in Zhouqu county of Gansu Province.
Cows in Zhouqu county developed symptom on 14th June. As of 20th June
[2006], 213 cows were sick. The reference lab of MOA confirmed this
was a Asia type I FMD outbreak on 19th June.
Measures have been taken by the local government and MOA. 380 sick
cows and cows were culled.
Translated from Chinese news from official site of Ministry Of
Agriculture of China at
<http://www.agri.gov.cn/ztzl/fkqlg/yqfb/t20060623_636093.htm>.
----
Yang Li
<yangli@neuro-hemin.com>

[This report suggests continuing outbreaks, even though Gansu
province has been previously reported. Since December 2005, there
have been outbreaks in ShanDong, Ningxia, Jiangxi, Gansu, Qinghai and
Hubei province.
For more detailed comments, see Mod.AS's comments in Foot & mouth
disease - China (07): Gansu, Hubei, susp 20060601.1527 referenced
below. Also, a map of China's provinces can be found at
<http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2003-02/19/content_815536.htm>. - Mod.PC]
